==Transportation==

===Railroad lines===
The Long Island Rail Road&#x27;s Main Line is the sole line within the Town of Riverhead. The only active station is Riverhead, which is also used as the western terminus of the Railroad Museum of Long Island.

===Bus service===
The Town of Riverhead is served primarily by Suffolk County Transit and Hampton Jitney bus routes.

===Major roads===

* Interstate 495 – New York
* New York State Route 25A – Stony Brook University
* New York State Route 25 – New York, Orient Point
* County Route 58 (Suffolk County, New York)
* County Route 105 (Suffolk County, New York)
*Sound Avenue

===Airports===
The town of Riverhead contains a minor private-use airport known as the Calverton Executive Airpark, originally the Naval Weapons Industrial Reserve Plant, Calverton.

